Issues.Body:
### System information

- **OS Windows 7**:
- **.NET Version 3.1.300**: 

### Issue

- **What did you do?** - I try to fit pipeline with byte[ ] columns.
- **What happened?** - I get "System.ArgumentOutOfRangeException: "Schema mismatch for feature column 'Features': expected Vector<Single>, got VarVector<Single> "".
- **What did you expect?** - I expected my model fitting with non-float data. In general, I want to load some muscial files into a model. And I want to get some data from model in byte[ ] type.

### Source code / logs

```
    class Program
    {
        static void Main(string[] args)
        {
            var mlContext = new MLContext();

            var testData = new TestData { Values = new byte[] { 1, 2 }, PredictedLabel = new byte[] { 3 } };
            var dataView = mlContext.Data.LoadFromEnumerable(new TestData[] { testData });
            var pipeline = mlContext.Transforms
                .CopyColumns("Label", "PredictedLabel")
                .Append(mlContext.Transforms.Concatenate("Features", "Values"))
                .Append(mlContext.Regression.Trainers.FastTree());

            var model = pipeline.Fit(dataView);
        }
        class TestData
        {
            public byte[] Values;

            public byte[] PredictedLabel;
        }

        class PredictedData
        {
            public byte[] PredictedLabel;
        }
    }
```

Trying to load a ML model from a stream (having the model as an embedded resource in the project), I get the below exception at mlContext.Model.Load() line. 

Same code snippet works if I load the model using the absolute filepath for the model.

Package Version: 1.5

